list.abstract: Male（英[ˈmɑːleɪ]，美[ˈmɑleɪ]），英语单词。做名词时，指男子、雄性植物、雄性动物等；做形容词时，指男性的、雄性的。例句为There were fewer and fewer male dinosaurs.（雄性恐龙越来越少）。

yingyinNormal.en: You had two full sets of organs, Jane. Female and male.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你有两套完整的器官，女性的和男性的。

yingyinNormal.en: No. But you know what? I think I need a male point of view.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还没，我决定问男性的意见。

yingyinNormal.en: But the reconstruction allowed us to create a male urinary tract. Further surgeries will be required.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但重塑手术可以重建一套男性的泌尿系统，后续还需要进一步手术。

yingyinNormal.en: You know what's not funny? Male pattern baldness.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道有什么是不好笑的吗？雄性秃头。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, I don't mind a male nanny, but I do draw the line at male wet nurse.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道的，我是不介意男保姆，但是我倒是很介意男的洗澡护士。

yingyinNormal.en: I didn't realize I was in an all-male club until that minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我直到这时才意识到自己来到了一家全男性俱乐部。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《Facebook COO谢丽尔·桑德伯格哈佛演讲》

yingyinNormal.en: I've arranged for Dame Nellie's accompanist to sleep with the male servants.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我安排内莉夫人的伴奏者，和男仆睡在一起。

yingyinNormal.en: This is something I long ago came to Peace with in my role as the beta male. Open.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很久以前，当我陷入爱河的时候我是可以打开的，快开。

yingyinNormal.en: When I fail to open this jar and you succeed, it will establish you as the alpha male.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当我没打开这瓶盖，而你打开了，这样你就像个男子汉。

yingyinNormal.en: I think he may need black male role models. Men who can show him who he might grow into.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我觉得他需要黑人男性榜样。让他知道长大后能成为什么样子的人。

yingyinNormal.en: His ideas about the male preoccupation with size might be of particular interest to you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他研究男性对尺寸的重视，你可能会有兴趣。

yingyinNormal.en: I think that's the best I can do. No male visitors after dark. So what did you bring me?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我尽我最大的努力了，天黑之后不允许男客进入。那么，你给我带了什么？

yingyinNormal.en: Camouflaging bald spots. That's primarily a male concern. Perhaps could expand our market.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当作遮羞的用途，这能够吸引男士目光，也许我们可以扩大市场。

yingyinNormal.en: Excuse me, Sheldon. How many reels before the sub-ordine male protagonist gets to the point?
yingyinNormal.zh: 打扰一下，谢尔顿，通常需要浪费多少卷胶片才能让次要的男主角说到重点上？

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, any male in his family, but Jeffrey Grant is the only one at the same school as Miss Littlejohn.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是的，家族中的任何男性，但杰弗里·格兰特是唯一和利特约翰小姐同校的家族成员。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, yes, like the male peacock with brilliant plumage or the rutting baboon with engorged hindquarters.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是啊，就像是雄孔雀那漂亮的羽毛，或者像发情的狒狒那饱满的臀部。

yingyinNormal.en: Ross. It was no big deal. We said that, the rumor was that you had both male and female reproductive parts.
yingyinNormal.zh: 罗斯。那真的没什么，我们说…那个谣言是…你同时有男性跟女性的生殖器官。

yingyinNormal.en: On the other hand, an adult Jewish male living with his mother is so common it borders on sociological cliché.
yingyinNormal.zh: 另一方面，一个成年犹太男性和母亲同住已经普遍到近似于社会学的陈词滥调了。

yingyinNormal.en: I mean, there are subsets like male and female, but apparently we're not as unique as we want to think we are.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我是说，就像可以分为男人女人这两种人一样，但很显然，我们不像我们想的那么独一无二。

yingyinNormal.en: What are you guys talking about? Rachel and I hired a male nanny. You got a man who's a nanny? You got a "manny"?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们在说些什么？瑞秋跟我雇了一个男保姆。你雇了一个男人当保姆？你雇了一个“男保”？

examination_example.sentence_trans: 离异的男性没有等待期就可以再婚，但女性则必须等待10个月才可以再婚。

examination_example.sentence: In Cambodia, the choice of a spouse is a complex one for the young <highlight>male</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在柬埔寨，对年轻男性来说，配偶的选择是一个复杂的问题。

examination_example.sentence: In <highlight>male</highlight>-dominated corporate America, sports is still a big deal.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在男性占主导地位的美国企业界，体育仍然是一件大事。
